@page "/components/data-display/card/accessibility"
@layout MainLayout
@using Sunfish.UIAdapters.Blazor.Components.Showcase

<PageTitle>Card / Accessibility · Sunfish Kitchen Sink</PageTitle>

<SunfishExamplePanel Title="Card / Accessibility"
                     Breadcrumb="@_breadcrumb"
                     GitHubUrl="https://github.com/ctwoodwa/Sunfish/blob/main/apps/kitchen-sink/Pages/Components/DataDisplay/Card/Accessibility/Demo.razor"
                     Sources="@GeneratedSources">

    <Narrative>
        <p>
            <code>SunfishCard</code> is a semantic container rather than a single interactive widget, so
            accessibility is driven by the content you place inside. Use landmark roles and headings where
            appropriate: a card that acts as a named section should carry <code>role="region"</code> and an
            <code>aria-labelledby</code> that points at its <code>SunfishCardHeader</code>. A card that is
            entirely clickable should expose a real <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> or link — do not rely on
            <code>onclick</code> on a plain <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>.
        </p>
        <p>
            When a card contains a media image, supply a descriptive <code>Alt</code> on
            <code>SunfishCardImage</code>. Decorative imagery should pass <code>Alt=""</code>. Action rows
            (<code>SunfishCardActions</code>) should carry enough label text on each button for screen-reader
            users to distinguish destructive actions from neutral ones — icon-only buttons need
            <code>aria-label</code>.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Keyboard</strong> — because the card itself is not focusable, keyboard navigation moves
            through the focusable descendants in DOM order (link → buttons → form fields). Ensure the
            visually-prominent primary action is also the first interactive element in the DOM so Tab lands
            there first.
        </p>
    </Narrative>

    <Example>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:1.25rem;">
            <div class="demo-row" style="gap:1rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
                <SunfishCard Width="320px" role="region" aria-labelledby="card-proj-alpha">
                    <SunfishCardHeader>
                        <span id="card-proj-alpha">Project Alpha</span>
                    </SunfishCardHeader>
                    <SunfishCardBody>
                        <p>This card exposes a named landmark via <code>role="region"</code> and
                        <code>aria-labelledby</code> referencing the header id.</p>
                    </SunfishCardBody>
                    <SunfishCardActions>
                        <SunfishButton Variant="ButtonVariant.Primary" Size="ButtonSize.Small" aria-label="Open Project Alpha">Open</SunfishButton>
                        <SunfishButton Variant="ButtonVariant.Danger" Size="ButtonSize.Small" aria-label="Archive Project Alpha">Archive</SunfishButton>
                    </SunfishCardActions>
                </SunfishCard>

                <SunfishCard Width="320px" role="region" aria-labelledby="card-media">
                    <SunfishCardImage Src="https://picsum.photos/seed/a11y-card/320/140" Alt="Quarterly revenue chart showing a rising trend across four quarters" />
                    <SunfishCardHeader>
                        <span id="card-media">Quarterly Report</span>
                    </SunfishCardHeader>
                    <SunfishCardBody>
                        <p>The media image carries a descriptive <code>Alt</code> so screen-reader users get
                        the same information sighted users do.</p>
                    </SunfishCardBody>
                </SunfishCard>
            </div>

            <dl style="font-size:0.875rem; max-width:640px;">
                <dt><strong>role</strong></dt>
                <dd>region (when card represents a named section), article (for self-contained feed items)</dd>
                <dt><strong>aria-labelledby</strong></dt>
                <dd>Points at the id of the element inside <code>SunfishCardHeader</code> that names the card.</dd>
                <dt><strong>Image alt text</strong></dt>
                <dd>Descriptive for meaningful visuals; empty <code>Alt=""</code> for decorative images.</dd>
                <dt><strong>Keyboard order</strong></dt>
                <dd>Tab traverses descendants in DOM order. Place the primary action first.</dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
    </Example>

</SunfishExamplePanel>

@code {
    private static readonly string[] _breadcrumb =
        ["Components", "Data Display", "Card", "Accessibility"];
}
